@*
    Shared "Last saved" timestamp — REQUIREMENTS §51.

    A tiny, consistent line shown next to a primary Save button telling the user
    when the row was last saved (the entity's UpdatedAt / last-saved field). With
    no saved-at value (never saved) it renders nothing, so a brand-new form stays
    clean.

    HOW TO USE (place right after the primary Save button):
        <partial name="_LastSaved" model="Model.SomeEntity.UpdatedAt" />

    The model is the nullable saved-at instant. Times are stored UTC; we show them
    in UTC with a clear suffix so there is no ambiguity (the hub has participants
    across time zones) — matching the existing "Last Sessionize import … UTC" copy.

    Mobile-first: a small, muted, wrapping inline line with no fixed height.
*@
@model DateTimeOffset?
@if (Model is { } savedAt)
{
    <p class="ceh-last-saved" style="font-size:12px;color:#6b7280;margin:6px 0 0;">
        Last saved @savedAt.ToUniversalTime().ToString("dd MMM yyyy HH:mm") UTC
    </p>
}
